  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>• To determine the maximum tolerated dose (MTD) and dose-limiting toxicity (DLT) of AMN107 as a single agent when administered as an oral once-daily and twice daily dose to adult patients with imatinib-resistant CML (phase l)</measure>
    <time_frame>study duration</time_frame>
  </primary_outcome>
  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>• To characterize the pharmacokinetic profile of AMN107 in serum and, where samples are available, in tumor cells and normal hematopoietic cells. (phase l)</measure>
    <time_frame>duration of study</time_frame>
  </primary_outcome>
  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>• To evaluate the efficacy and safety of AMN107 in patients with imatinib-resistant or intolerant CML-BC, imatinib-resistant or intolerant CML-AP and imatinib-resistant or intolerant CML-CP. (phase ll)</measure>
    <time_frame>duration of study</time_frame>
  </primary_outcome>
  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>• To evaluate safety and preliminary anticancer activity of AMN107 in relapsed/refractory patients with Ph+ ALL, HES/CEL and SM. (phase ll)</measure>
    <time_frame>duration of study</time_frame>
  </primary_outcome>
  <secondary_outcome>
    <measure>To assess changes during and after therapy in malignant cells taken from the bone marrow and/or blood.(phase ll)</measure>
    <time_frame>study duration</time_frame>
  </secondary_outcome>
  <secondary_outcome>
    <measure>To evaluate the population pharmacokinetics of AMN107 (all arms of the study) (phase ll)</measure>
    <time_frame>study duration</time_frame>
  </secondary_outcome>
  <secondary_outcome>
    <measure>To examine whether individual genetic variation in genes relating to drug metabolism, CML and the drug pathway confer differential response to AMN107 (phase ll)</measure>
    <time_frame>study duration</time_frame>
  </secondary_outcome>
  <secondary_outcome>
    <measure>To identify gene expression patterns in tumor cells that are associated with treatment response to AMN107 or that correlate with the severity or progression of CML. (phase ll)</measure>
    <time_frame>study duration</time_frame>
  </secondary_outcome>
